From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000001 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: ETNA workload generator <etna@local>
Date: Thu, 1 May 2026 03:30:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] synthesised: don't crash on numeric entities above maxBound

Mirrors the historical fix at f2dcaa682c6d5f7dea34eb09bb5b02532be523c9
("Don't crash on malformed characters, replace them with ?") which has
since been re-implemented as an inRange check inside lookupNumericEntity.
The buggy variant removes the inRange check, so the unguarded `chr` call
raises Prelude.chr: bad argument for any numeric entity > 0x10FFFF.

---
 src/Text/HTML/TagSoup/Entity.hs | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/src/Text/HTML/TagSoup/Entity.hs b/src/Text/HTML/TagSoup/Entity.hs
index 0000000..0000001 100644
--- a/src/Text/HTML/TagSoup/Entity.hs
+++ b/src/Text/HTML/TagSoup/Entity.hs
@@ -43,6 +43,7 @@ lookupNumericEntity = f
             test $ not $ null xs
             case reader xs of
                 [(a,"")] -> do
+                    test $ inRange (toInteger $ ord minBound, toInteger $ ord maxBound) a
                     return [chr $ fromInteger a]
                 _ -> Nothing

